## Summary

The `desktop:getVersion` IPC handler was registered in `desktop.ts` (line 751) but was never exposed in the `electronAPI` object in `preload.ts`, causing `window.electronAPI.getAppVersion()` to be `undefined` in the renderer.

## Fix

Added `getAppVersion` method to `electronAPI` in `packages/milaidy/apps/app/electron/src/preload.ts` that calls `ipcRenderer.invoke('desktop:getVersion')`.

The method returns:
```ts
{
  version: string;
  name: string;
  electron: string;
  chrome: string;
  node: string;
}
```

## Testing

Call from renderer:
```ts
const versionInfo = await window.electronAPI.getAppVersion();
console.log(versionInfo.version);
```

Fixes elizaOS/eliza#6617
